criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. 20-39 years old who had infertility for more than 1 year and had clinical palpable
             varicoceles;

          2. impaired semen quality including sperm concentration <15 million/ml or total motility
             <40% or progressively motile < 32% (a+b), the 5th edited World Health Organization
             criteria was referred;

          3. with normal level of serum hormones including follicle stimulating hormone,
             luteinizing hormone, Thyroid hormones and prolactin;

          4. patient's spouse was healthy in reproduction.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. with subclinical varicocele, recurrent varicoceles;

          2. normal semen analyses;

          3. other reasons of infertility than varicoceles;

          4. refusing to enter randomization;

          5. female partner older than 35 years;

          6. with abnormal level of serum hormones;

          7. female factor infertility;

          8. with significant surgical diseases, congenital diseases or endocrine diseases.
